00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:04,240
So, that's the first major difference between our world
所以，这就是我们世界与他们世界的第一个主要区别。

654
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:06,440
and their world.
与他们世界。

655
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:08,700
We've been taught that
我们被教导为…

656
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:13,540
nature is our enemy or nature is outside us,
自然是我们的敌人或自然在我们之外，

657
00:40:13,660 --> 00:40:16,220
whereas they believe that they are part of nature.
而他们则认为自己是自然的一部分。

658
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,280
Okay? Does that make sense, guys?
好吧？这样说通吗，大家？

659
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:25,260
Alright, let's move on. Alright.
好的，接着说。

660
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:29,200
So, this is about
所以，这个是关于

661
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:31,600
their religious practice, okay?
他们的宗教实践，好的？

662
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:34,940
So, they have a meal together and then
于是他们一起吃饭，然后

663
00:40:35,420 --> 00:40:36,840
they sing
他们便开始歌唱

664
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:41,180
or they use the malomo to make noises and they sing and dance, okay?
或者他们用马洛莫发出声音，然后唱歌跳舞，好吗？

665
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:44,800
Everyone ate his fill as and when he pleased.
每个人吃到饱为止，随心所欲。

666
00:40:45,020 --> 00:40:48,520
A couple of the older men saying they would
一两位年长的男子说他们会等到小孩儿吃完再吃。

667
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:51,340
wait until the youngsters had finished before they ate.
他们说会等到小孩儿吃完再吃。

668
00:40:51,620 --> 00:40:54,240
But they did not wait for long.
但他们并没有等很久。

669
00:40:54,540 --> 00:40:58,840
I was told, however, that everyone had to eat just as no adult male
我被告知，然而每个人都必须随时吃饭。

670
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:02,280
was allowed to sleep, but to sing while
被允许睡觉，但在唱歌时……

671
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:04,740
malomo was singing was in progress.
马洛莫正在唱歌的过程中……

672
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:08,880
Apparently, one of the greatest crimes that a pygmy can commit,
显然，最重大的小人犯下的罪行，若非最重大的话，便是被发现睡着时，马洛莫正在唱歌。

673
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:13,380
if not the greatest, is to be found asleep when the malomo is singing.
显然，最重大的小人犯下的罪行，若非最重大的话，便是被发现睡着时，马洛莫正在唱歌。

674
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:17,660
One of the men stood up and miming, as all pygmies love to do,
一名男子站起，像所有小人一样做了个手势，

675
00:41:17,820 --> 00:41:20,880
he showed how they used to search for sleeping men,
他示范了他们寻找睡着的人的方式。

676
00:41:21,100 --> 00:41:24,460
a spear under each arm, and how if they found one,
每只手臂下放一支矛，若他们发现一人，他们会把矛刺进他的腹部，彻底杀死他。我听说那时他的尸体…

677
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:28,380
they would spear him in the stomach and kill him completely and forever.
每只手臂下放一支矛，若他们发现一人，他们会把矛刺进他的腹部，彻底杀死他。我听说那时他的尸体…

678
00:41:28,620 --> 00:41:30,900
I was told that then his body
I was told thatthen his body

679
00:41:31,420 --> 00:41:33,880
would be buried under the komalamo,
被埋在科马拉莫之下

680
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:38,780
okay, the komalamo is a great fire in which they practice their religion, okay?
好的，科马拉莫是一场大火，他们在其中进行宗教仪式，好吗？

681
00:41:38,940 --> 00:41:42,480
And nobody would be allowed to mention his death,
没有人能提及他的死亡

682
00:41:42,620 --> 00:41:44,180
even to remark on his absence.
甚至提到他的缺席。

683
00:41:44,540 --> 00:41:46,920
The woman would be told that the malomo
女子会被告知，malomo本身，森林的伟大动物，

684
00:41:47,540 --> 00:41:50,180
itself, the great animal of the forest,
itself, the great animal of the forest,

685
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:53,720
had carried off one of their number, but like the men,
被带走了他们中的一个，但像男人一样，

686
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:58,380
they would ask no questions and would never again mention the missing men.
他们不问问题，也不再提起失踪的男人。

687
00:41:58,740 --> 00:42:01,120
Okay. So in this world,
好的。所以在这个世界里。

688
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:04,920
the greatest crime you can commit is not to kill someone,
你能犯下的最大罪行就是不杀人。

689
00:42:05,860 --> 00:42:10,180
but to sleep during the religion.
但在宗教中睡觉。

690
00:42:11,940 --> 00:42:15,300
Can someone explain why that's the case?
有人能解释为什么会这样吗？

691
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:21,800
In this world, okay, the pygmy world, the worst thing you can do is sleep.
在这个世界里，好的，侏儒世界，最糟的事就是睡觉。

692
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:26,760
Why is that the case?
为什么会这样呢？

693
00:42:31,180 --> 00:42:35,020
Okay. Let's just say that we're having a class,
好的。我们先说我们在上课，

694
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,460
and one of you is sleeping, okay?
其中有人在睡觉，好的？

695
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:41,000
And I get so angry
我会很生气我想要杀了他。

696
00:42:42,040 --> 00:42:43,500
that I want to kill that person.
我会很生气我想要杀了他。

697
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:46,740
Why would I want to do that? What's my logic?
我为什么想这么做？我的逻辑是什么？

698
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:50,100
It's disrespectful of what?
这是什么不敬之处？

699
00:42:51,860 --> 00:42:54,880
Okay, it's disrespectful of my authority, that
好的，这算是对我的权威不敬

700
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:56,760
is true, but then I just
是的，但随后我只是

701
00:42:57,180 --> 00:42:59,040
ask a person to leave my class, right?
请人离开我的课堂，对吧？

702
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:01,780
Or I shout at that person, but I want to kill that person.
或者我大喊那人，我想杀那人。

703
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,840
Why? What's happened?
为什么？发生了什么？

704
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,620
Okay. Okay.
好的。好的。

705
00:43:09,620 --> 00:43:13,440
What is a classroom? What is a classroom?
什么是教室？什么是教室？

706
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:21,260
Okay. A place to study.
好的。一个学习的地方。

707
00:43:21,340 --> 00:43:24,420
What else? What are we doing now?
还有什么？我们现在在做什么？

708
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,460
Yeah, but what is class? What is classroom?
是的，但什么是课堂？什么是教室？

709
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:38,300
What allows a classroom to exist? What allows a classroom to exist?
什么让教室得以存在？什么让教室得以存在？

710
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:52,480
Hmm? What is the ritual we're practicing?
嗯？我们正在练习的仪式是什么？

711
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:57,960
Okay, so a classroom, you can understand as the collective experience,
好的，教室可以理解为集体经验，

712
00:43:58,380 --> 00:44:02,360
okay? A classroom happens when everyone is participating in it.
好的？教室就是大家一起参与时才会出现。

713
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:05,400
Does that make sense? That's why we take classroom alive.
这样说通吗？这就是我们让教室活起来的原因。

714
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:10,700
So why would I be angry if one of you is sleeping?
那我为什么会生气，如果你们中有人睡着呢？

715
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:17,340
But why does that matter?
那又为什么重要？

716
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:20,800
......
....

717
00:44:23,460 --> 00:44:25,740
......
......

718
00:44:25,740 --> 00:44:27,540
If you're sleeping, what are you telling me?
如果你睡着，跟我说的是什么？

719
00:44:29,540 --> 00:44:33,160
... Yeah, it's not a classroom.
…是的，没成教室。

720
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:36,340
It's not real. This discussion is not real.
这不是现实的。这次讨论也是如此。

721
00:44:36,460 --> 00:44:38,340
It's pointless. You understand?
这没意义。你明白吗？

722
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:40,640
So that's what's happening here.
于是这里就发生了这些事。

723
00:44:41,180 --> 00:44:43,960
Their malemo singing, the ritual,
他们的 malemo 唱歌，仪式，

724
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:48,560
it's meant for everyone to recognize that the religion is real.
它的设定是让大家认识到宗教是真实。

725
00:44:48,700 --> 00:44:50,060
It's more real than reality.
它比现实更真实。

726
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:54,600
Okay? But if you're sleeping, you're saying, no guys, this doesn't matter, okay?
好的？但如果你在睡觉，你就说，没事，伙计们，这不重要，好吗？

727
00:44:54,740 --> 00:44:56,620
What we're doing does not matter.
我们正在做的事不重要。

728
00:44:57,580 --> 00:45:00,200
And therefore, what you're doing is,
于是，你所做的事是，

729
00:45:00,420 --> 00:45:03,660
you're not committing violence on one person,
你并没有对一个人造成暴力。

730
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:05,960
you're committing violence on the community.
你正在对社区施暴力。

731
00:45:07,080 --> 00:45:09,040
You're committing violence on the religion.
你正在对宗教施暴力。

732
00:45:09,380 --> 00:45:11,400
You're insulting the forest.
你在侮辱森林。

733
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:13,020
You're insulting the god.
你在侮辱神。

734
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:16,040
Does that make sense? And that's the word for the worst crime.
这有道理吗？这就是“最坏的”词。

735
00:45:17,430 --> 00:45:19,000
Because reality happens.
因为现实就发生了。

736
00:45:19,120 --> 00:45:21,000
This religion is only possible
这宗教才有可能

737
00:45:21,390 --> 00:45:24,140
if everyone believes that it is true.
如果大家都相信它是真的。

738
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:28,280
If you're sleeping, it means you don't think it's true.
如果你在睡觉，那就说明你不认为它是真的。

739
00:45:29,480 --> 00:45:32,000
And therefore, you are,
于是，你们是，

740
00:45:32,780 --> 00:45:35,440
first of all, rejecting the community, right?
首先，离开社区，对吧？

741
00:45:35,640 --> 00:45:37,460
You're telling everyone, you're all idiots.
你在跟大家说，你们都是傻瓜。

742
00:45:38,020 --> 00:45:40,880
Okay? Second is that you might
好的？第二点是你可能

743
00:45:41,570 --> 00:45:44,520
endanger the community because you're insulting the forest.
因为你侮辱森林而危及社区。

744
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:48,280
Does that make sense, guys? Okay?
那有道理吗，大家？好吧？

745
00:45:48,380 --> 00:45:50,340
So for most of human history,
所以在大部分人类历史里，

746
00:45:51,780 --> 00:45:54,520
people take their religion extremely seriously.
人们把自己的宗教极其认真。

747
00:45:55,340 --> 00:45:58,960
So seriously that they think it's more real than
如此认真，以至认为它比……更真实。

748
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:03,160
reality. As long as everyone believes in it, it's true.
现实。只要大家都相信它，它就是真的。

749
00:46:03,380 --> 00:46:06,180
But if someone doesn't believe in it, then we have to kill that person.
但若有人不相信它，我们就得把那个人杀掉。

750
00:46:06,340 --> 00:46:10,840
Because if he doesn't believe in it, then it might cause our religion to die.
因为如果他不相信它，就会导致我们的宗教死亡。

751
00:46:11,020 --> 00:46:13,620
Okay? Does that make sense? Any questions so far?
好的？这样说通吗？到现在还有问题吗？

752
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,080
Any questions?
还有问题吗？

753
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:19,260
We're all clear, right? Okay?
我们都明白了吧？

754
00:46:19,700 --> 00:46:23,460
And what I'm trying to show you is the power of religion.
我想给你们展示的是宗教的力量。

755
00:46:23,660 --> 00:46:26,720
Okay? How once we have the religious imagination,
好？一旦我们拥有宗教想象，

756
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:30,840
we can create things that are actually for us more real
我们可以创造的东西，实际上对我们更真实

757
00:46:31,480 --> 00:46:33,760
than reality. Okay? So
比现实更… 好吗？所以

758
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:35,920
that's the second thing that's different
第二点与其他人类不同

759
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:40,060
about us from other human beings.
关于我们的区别

760
00:46:40,120 --> 00:46:43,960
For most of human history, we were spiritual.
在大部分人类历史里，我们是灵性的。

761
00:46:44,320 --> 00:46:48,900
Okay? We were spiritual meaning like we believe like the world of spirits,
好？我们是灵性的，意思是我们相信灵界。

762
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,400
our soul, it exists.
我们的灵魂，它存在。

763
00:46:51,740 --> 00:46:54,760
Okay? Today the word we use is
好了？今天我们使用的词是

764
00:46:56,180 --> 00:46:59,480
materialistic. Materialistic.
唯物主义的。唯物主义的。

765
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:01,860
And the idea of materialistic is this.
而唯物主义的概念是这样的。

766
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:05,140
If we cannot see it, okay, it's not real.
如果我们看不见它，好了，它就不是真的。

767
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:09,640
Okay? God can't be real because we can't find it.
好？上帝看不见它，它就不是真的。

768
00:47:09,740 --> 00:47:13,240
The soul can't be real because we can't measure it.
灵魂之能测量，故其可为真。

769
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:16,480
Imagination can't be real because
想象之能测量，故其可为真。

770
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:18,520
we don't know where it comes from.
我们不知道它来自哪里。

771
00:47:18,700 --> 00:47:20,700
Okay? Does that make sense? And obviously,
好？这有道理吗？显然，

772
00:47:21,060 --> 00:47:25,360
okay, obviously, this idea of materialism is wrong.
好，显然，这个唯物主义的概念是错的。

773
00:47:25,940 --> 00:47:30,000
How can you say the imagination doesn't exist?
想象怎么会不存在？

774
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:36,300
But unfortunately, we have structured our society around this idea.
可惜的是，我们把社会组织在这个想法上。

775
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:39,580
All of science, okay, when you go to science class, they teach you this.
科学全都如此，去上科学课就会学到这点。

776
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:42,940
Okay? If it's real, you can measure it.
好的？如果它是真的，你可以测量它。

777
00:47:43,060 --> 00:47:46,360
You can see it. You can feel it.
你可以看到它。你可以感受它。

778
00:47:46,940 --> 00:47:50,120
But for most of human history, we didn't believe that.
但在大多数人类历史里，我们并不相信这一点。

779
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:53,460
We thought like, okay, there is a spiritual world
我们想，好的，存在一个灵性世界

780
00:47:53,920 --> 00:47:56,000
and that matters just as much as reality.
而且它和现实一样重要

781
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:58,960
Okay? In fact, it probably matters more
好的？实际上，它可能更重要

782
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:02,800
than reality. Okay?
比现实更重要。好的吗？

783
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:06,220
So, this is making sense, right guys? Okay.
所以，这样说就有道理了，对吧，大家？好。

784
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:14,860
Okay. For a month,
好。持续一个月，

785
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:19,020
I sat every evening at the Kamal Molo listening, watching, okay?
我每晚坐在卡马尔·莫洛旁边听着，看的，行吗？

786
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:23,000
If I still had little idea of what was going on,
如果我还对发生的事有一点点想法，

787
00:48:23,180 --> 00:48:26,880
at least I felt that ear of importance and expectancy.
至少我能感受到那种重要与期待的耳朵。

788
00:48:27,580 --> 00:48:30,360
Every evening, when the woman shut themselves up,
每晚，女人关上门时，

789
00:48:30,540 --> 00:48:34,120
pretending that they were afraid to see the animal in the forest.
假装他们怕在森林里看到动物。

790
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:37,700
Every evening, when the man gathered around the fire,
每晚，男人围着火堆聚集时。

791
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:40,560
pretending they thought that the woman thought
假装他们以为女人认为

792
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:42,860
that the drain pipes were animals.
假装他们以为女人认为排水管是动物

793
00:48:43,140 --> 00:48:45,060
Every evening, when the trumpet dropped,
每晚，号角落下时

794
00:48:45,660 --> 00:48:49,600
the drain pipes imitated leopards and elephants and buffaloes.
排水管像豹子、象和水牛一样

795
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:54,280
Every evening, when all this make -believe was going on,
每晚，当这一切全都在进行时

796
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:59,240
I felt that something very real and very great was going on beneath it.
我感觉到有一件非常真实、非常伟大的事在其下方进行

797
00:48:59,380 --> 00:49:02,880
Something that everyone else took for granted and about
一件大家都视为理所当然的事，关于……

798
00:49:03,420 --> 00:49:04,740
which only I was ignorant.
只有我才是无知的。

799
00:49:05,460 --> 00:49:09,260
Okay. Clearly, he does not understand these people.
好的。显然，他完全不懂这些人。

800
00:49:09,440 --> 00:49:12,360
What word tells us he does not understand these people?
什么词告诉我们他不懂这些人？

801
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,200
He doesn't know what's going on.
他不知道发生了什么事。

802
00:49:15,300 --> 00:49:17,460
Why? What word tells us this?
为什么？什么词告诉我们这个？

803
00:49:19,300 --> 00:49:21,740
Excuse me? Why is he ignorant?
请问一下？他为什么会无知？

804
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:27,420
There's a word in here that tells us he doesn't understand these people at all.
这里有个词告诉我们他完全不懂这些人。

805
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:35,960
This word shows that
这个词表明了这一点。

806
00:49:36,980 --> 00:49:38,400
there's a chasm, okay?
有个深坑，行吗？

807
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:42,080
A huge difference between the pygmies and us.
比比姆与我们的差距大得很。

808
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:45,960
What is this word? It's a word that the pygmies use.
这个词是什么？是比比姆用的词。

809
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:47,920
What word would the pygmies not use here?
什么词是比比姆不想用的？

810
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:50,480
They'd be insulted by this word.
他们会被这词冒犯的。

811
00:49:54,040 --> 00:49:57,240
What's the word? You use it over and over again, right?
这个词是什么？你一遍又一遍地用，对吧？

812
00:49:57,460 --> 00:49:58,920
There's a word here that's insulting.
这里有个词很冒犯。

813
00:50:02,880 --> 00:50:06,480
No. What word here
不。这里的哪个词？

814
00:50:07,020 --> 00:50:09,780
in this passage would the pygmies find insulting?
在这段话里，哪一个词会让比比姆觉得冒犯？

815
00:50:11,660 --> 00:50:15,640
No. What word here
不。这里的哪个词？

816
00:50:19,360 --> 00:50:22,580
is insulting? So if another teacher comes into
是哪个词？

817
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:28,600
my class and he says, wow, your class is a lot of fun.
我的班级，他说，哇，你的班级很有趣。

818
00:50:30,140 --> 00:50:31,340
I'd be insulted. Why?
我会被冒犯。为什么？

819
00:50:33,900 --> 00:50:38,220
I'd be insulted. Why? No.
我会被冒犯。为什么？不。

820
00:50:41,700 --> 00:50:43,620
Wow, you guys have so much fun in this class.
哇，你们这班真有趣。

821
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:47,340
I've been insulted, why?
我被冒犯了，为什么？

822
00:50:52,660 --> 00:50:57,020
Excuse me? Yeah, this is not studying, okay?
请问一下？是的，这不是学习，好的？

823
00:50:57,140 --> 00:50:59,980
This is not serious academic work.
这不是正式的学术工作。

824
00:51:00,180 --> 00:51:02,560
This is playing. It has no significance,
这是一种游戏，没什么意义。

825
00:51:02,920 --> 00:51:04,720
no meaning, right?
没有意义，对吧？

826
00:51:05,400 --> 00:51:08,180
So what word implies that here?
那么这里用什么词来表示呢？

827
00:51:13,300 --> 00:51:14,900
It repeats itself over and over.
它一遍又一遍地重复。

828
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:21,740
Pretending, right? Pretending.
假装，对吧？假装。

829
00:51:23,120 --> 00:51:24,560
We think they're playing.
我们认为他们在玩耍。

830
00:51:24,860 --> 00:51:25,760
What do they think?
他们在想什么？

831
00:51:30,500 --> 00:51:32,540
We think they're pretending. We think they're playing.
我们认为他们在假装。我们认为他们在玩耍。

832
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:37,600
What do they think? They think it's all true, do you understand?
他们在想什么？他们认为这一切都是真的，你明白吗？

833
00:51:38,180 --> 00:51:41,960
For them, their religion is more true than this world,
对他们来说，他们的宗教比这世界更真实。

834
00:51:42,140 --> 00:51:43,620
okay?
好吗？

835
00:51:44,300 --> 00:51:46,760
That's a power of the human imagination.
这就是人类想象的力量。

836
00:51:47,400 --> 00:51:50,140
You can imagine a world, and this world,
你可以想象一个世界，这个世界，

837
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,840
as long as many of you are imagining it together,
只要你们许多人一起想象它，

838
00:51:53,540 --> 00:51:56,180
it's more true, more powerful,
更真实，更强大，

839
00:51:56,320 --> 00:51:58,340
more real than this world.
比这世界更真实。

840
00:51:58,560 --> 00:52:00,380
That's a power of religion, okay?
这就是宗教的力量，好的？

841
00:52:00,640 --> 00:52:02,120
What we call the religious imagination.
我们所说的宗教想象。

842
00:52:02,660 --> 00:52:05,620
And we'll see this over and over again in human history, okay?
我们会在历史中一次又一次看到这一点，好的？

843
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,520
Does that make sense, guys? Okay?
这有道理吗，大家？好的？

844
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:11,740
So we've been taught that oh, you can't see it.
所以我们被教导，哦，你看不见它。

845
00:52:11,860 --> 00:52:13,300
It must be pretending.
这一定是伪装。

846
00:52:13,860 --> 00:52:15,940
It must be make -believe.
它一定是让人相信的。

847
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:19,740
But for most of human history, for most people,
但在大部分人类历史中，在大多数人中，

848
00:52:19,940 --> 00:52:22,120
this is not playing.
这不是在玩。

849
00:52:22,360 --> 00:52:24,460
This is not pretending. It's true.
这不是伪装。它是真的。

850
00:52:24,620 --> 00:52:28,440
It's real. It's what allows us to be close to God,
它是真的。它让我们能靠近上帝。

851
00:52:28,640 --> 00:52:29,840
okay?
好的？

852
00:52:29,940 --> 00:52:34,460
God is real. This world we live in, it's not real.
上帝是真的。我们所居住的这世界，却不是实在。

853
00:52:35,620 --> 00:52:39,200
Okay? Does that make sense, guys? All right.
好？这样说通吗，大家？没问题。

854
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:49,000
Okay, so let's look at the last paragraph, and then we'll finish for the day.
好的，那我们先看最后一段，然后结束今天的工作。

855
00:52:49,420 --> 00:52:50,660
He went on to tell that
他继续说……

856
00:52:50,660 --> 00:52:54,560
the pygmies called their malomo whenever things seemed to be going wrong.
比姆人把他们的malomo称作当事物似乎走错路时。

857
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:57,480
It may be that the hunting is bad, he said,
他可能是说狩猎不顺利。

858
00:52:57,780 --> 00:53:02,300
or that someone is ill, or, as now, that someone has died.
或者有人生病，或者现在有人去世。

859
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:05,660
These are not good things, and we like things to be good.
这些事不算好事，我们喜欢好事。

860
00:53:05,660 --> 00:53:08,160
So we call out the malomo, and
于是我们呼唤 malomo，

861
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:11,420
it makes them good as they should be, okay?
让它们变得如其本应之好，明白吗？

862
00:53:11,540 --> 00:53:16,180
So this is very similar to the shaman going into the spirit world
所以这与萨满进入灵界非常相似

863
00:53:16,180 --> 00:53:18,620
when things are bad, okay?
当事物不顺利时，好吗？

864
00:53:18,880 --> 00:53:21,980
Things are bad because the spirits are unhappy.
事物不顺利是因为灵魂不安

865
00:53:24,880 --> 00:53:28,160
Normally, everything goes well in our world, in our forest,
通常，在我们的世界里，在我们的森林里，一切都顺利。

866
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:30,760
but at night when we are sleeping,
但在夜里我们睡觉时，

867
00:53:30,980 --> 00:53:35,560
sometimes things go wrong because we are not awake.
有时事物会出错，因为我们没醒

868
00:53:35,660 --> 00:53:37,920
To stop them from going wrong.
为止它们走错。

869
00:53:38,750 --> 00:53:40,560
Army ants invade the camp.
军蚁入营。

870
00:53:40,880 --> 00:53:45,400
Leopards may come in and steal a hunting dog or even a child.
豹子可能会闯进来，偷走猎犬甚至孩子。

871
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:49,240
If we were awake, these things would not happen.
若我们醒着，这些事就不会发生。

872
00:53:49,380 --> 00:53:51,440
So when something big goes wrong,
于是当大事出错时，

873
00:53:51,660 --> 00:53:54,960
like illness or bad hunting or death,
就像疾病、捕猎失败或死亡一样，

874
00:53:55,180 --> 00:53:58,140
it must be because the forest is sleeping and
它一定是因为森林在睡觉而

875
00:53:58,140 --> 00:54:00,280
not looking after its children.
没有照顾它的孩子们。

876
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:03,420
So what do we do? We wake it up.
那我们怎么做？我们把它唤醒。

877
00:54:03,460 --> 00:54:05,520
We wake it up by singing to it.
我们通过唱歌来唤醒它。

878
00:54:05,660 --> 00:54:09,160
and we do this because we want it to awaken happy,
我们这样做是因为想让它醒来时充满喜悦

879
00:54:09,420 --> 00:54:12,560
then everything will be well and good again.
然后一切都会再次安好。

880
00:54:12,680 --> 00:54:15,100
So when our world is going well,
当我们的世界运转顺利时，

881
00:54:15,680 --> 00:54:18,520
then also we sing to the forest
我们也会为森林歌唱

882
00:54:18,520 --> 00:54:21,480
because we want it to share our happiness, okay?
因为我们想让它分享我们的喜悦，好吗？

883
00:54:22,180 --> 00:54:25,880
Do you understand? So this is like them going to the spirit world
你明白了吗？这就像他们去灵界一样。

884
00:54:25,880 --> 00:54:27,840
and communicating with the spirits.
并与灵体沟通。

885
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:30,040
So it's almost the same religion, okay?
所以它几乎是同一种宗教，好吗？

886
00:54:31,260 --> 00:54:34,760
Maybe the details are different, but the idea is the same.
也许细节不同，但思路相同。

887
00:54:35,660 --> 00:54:37,320
The idea is that we're all interconnected.
思路是我们彼此相连。

888
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:41,480
Animals, plants, humans, all the same.
动物、植物、人类，皆同一体。

889
00:54:42,700 --> 00:54:44,140
This is not the real world.
这才是真实世界。

890
00:54:44,260 --> 00:54:48,140
The spirit world, the forest, they're the real world.
灵界、森林，它们才是真实世界。

891
00:54:48,940 --> 00:54:52,880
And for us to maintain our health
而我们保持健康的方式是……

892
00:54:52,880 --> 00:54:54,420
and our happiness and our safety,
以及我们的幸福与安全，

893
00:54:54,540 --> 00:54:59,780
we must always communicate with this other world
我们必须始终与这另一世界沟通，

894
00:54:59,780 --> 00:55:01,740
and make sure they're happy.
并确保它们的喜乐。

895
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:07,200
Okay, does it make sense? And
好的，听得懂吗？然后

896
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:09,120
because of this belief,
因为这个信念，

897
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:12,500
it means we shouldn't go to war with other people, okay?
这意味着我们不该与别人开战，好吗？

898
00:55:12,700 --> 00:55:17,140
Because then that causes mayhem
因为这样就会造成混乱

899
00:55:17,140 --> 00:55:19,500
and chaos in the spirit world.
以及灵界的混沌

900
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:22,500
Our job is to maintain harmony and balance in this world.
我们的工作是维持此界的和谐与平衡

901
00:55:22,600 --> 00:55:23,840
We're caretakers, okay?
我们是看护者，好吗？

902
00:55:24,820 --> 00:55:28,280
It means we should not be in conflict with each other.
这意味着我们彼此不冲突。

903
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:30,820
We should be egalitarian. We should be equal because
我们要平等，彼此相等。

904
00:55:30,820 --> 00:55:33,560
we're all from the same mother goddess.
我们都来自同一位母神。

905
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:35,640
We're all from the same forest. We're all from...
我们都来自同一片森林。我们都来自……

906
00:55:35,660 --> 00:55:37,900
We're all from the same woman shaman, okay?
我们都来自同一位女巫师，好的？

907
00:55:38,480 --> 00:55:41,420
It means we have to be artistic because we have to celebrate
它意味着我们要有艺术性，因为我们要庆祝并崇拜灵界。

908
00:55:43,360 --> 00:55:46,040
and worship the spirit world.
这有道理吗？再说一次，…

909
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,740
Does that make sense? So again,
Does that make sense? So again,

910
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:51,920
for most of human history, we were like this.
在大多数人类历史中，我们就是这样。

911
00:55:52,020 --> 00:55:56,100
And even today, in a lot of cultures around the world, they're still like this.
即便到今天，世界上许多文化仍然是如此。

912
00:55:57,440 --> 00:55:58,840
So now the question is,
于是现在的问题是，

913
00:56:01,140 --> 00:56:03,720
what changed? Why do we have war?
什么改变了？我们为什么会有战争？

914
00:56:04,340 --> 00:56:05,700
Why do we have... Why do we have hierarchy?
我们为什么会有……我们为什么会有层级？

915
00:56:06,640 --> 00:56:08,500
Why do we have patriarchy?
我们为什么会有父系制？

916
00:56:08,780 --> 00:56:10,380
Why are men superior to women?
男人为何优于女人？

917
00:56:10,960 --> 00:56:14,620
Why do some rich people have all the power, okay?
为什么有些富人掌握全部权力？

918
00:56:14,820 --> 00:56:18,440
This clearly goes against this religion. And
这显然与此宗教相反。

919
00:56:18,440 --> 00:56:24,280
what I will show you starting next class is the beginning of a new religion
接下来上课我会展示的，是一种新宗教的起点

920
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:27,800
and how this new religion that
以及这新宗教的样子

921
00:56:27,800 --> 00:56:29,340
worships wealth,
它崇拜财富，

922
00:56:31,020 --> 00:56:34,660
power, and war conquered everyone, okay?
权力与战争征服了所有人，行吗？

923
00:56:35,440 --> 00:56:37,740
Does that make sense? Okay, any questions?
这样说通吗？行，任何问题吗？

924
00:56:39,720 --> 00:56:41,000
Before we break...
在我们开始之前……

925
00:56:42,940 --> 00:56:44,060
Anything you're unclear about?
还有什么不清楚的吗？

926
00:56:48,760 --> 00:56:52,420
Okay. Okay. Okay.
好的。好的。好的。
